Your professionalism inspired me to work hard at my current job too.

30
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:37,130
Although I wasn‚Äôt planning to buy any flowers, I went to your shop to see you.

31
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:44,880
I'd suggest not dropping by anymore then.

32
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:48,100
Although I'll maintain my professionalism,

33
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:52,110
having non-paying customers is hard for me,

34
00:02:52,110 --> 00:02:53,940
at least for now.

35
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:59,940
I‚Äôm fine as long as you‚Äôre happy.

36
00:03:02,990 --> 00:03:05,220
You are happy, aren't you?

37
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:11,570
Good.

38
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:20,090
Take care.

39
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,640
Thanks.

40
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:26,750
You, too.

41
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,720
Ritsu.

42
00:04:35,690 --> 00:04:37,730
Makoto-san.

43
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:43,940
I haven't worn something like this in a while.

44
00:04:43,940 --> 00:04:46,560
You look beautiful.

45
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,480
I want a charge.

46
00:04:55,970 --> 00:04:57,450
Here.

47
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,010
Makoto-san.

48
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:02,860
Don't, that's embarrassing.

49
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:04,300
Then how about this?

50
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:12,500
- Nice photo.
- We look like we're having fun.

51
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:15,380
We are having fun... right?

52
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:17,000
Yes.

53
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,600
Let's look over there.

54
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:46,180
Great timing, Makoto-chan.

55
00:05:48,430 --> 00:05:51,350
I was off visiting home for a while.

56
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:53,840
So you're from Yamagata (Kae speaks with an accent here).

57
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:58,610
And I hear you began going out with Ritsu-kun while I was gone.

58
00:05:58,610 --> 00:06:04,370
- Yes.
- So I guess those date clothes were to his taste.

59
00:06:04,370 --> 00:06:09,760
I'm glad he liked the dress after making him suffer so long.

60
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,670
I see. Did you have fun?

61
00:06:11,670 --> 00:06:14,930
He really tried hard to make it fun for me.

62
00:06:14,930 --> 00:06:18,110
So did you actually have fun?

63
00:06:21,030 --> 00:06:23,260
How are things with Kotaro-san?

64
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:27,010
I don't think I'll be seeing him anymore.

65
00:06:27,010 --> 00:06:31,720
I was sort of rude and ended up hurting him.

66
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:38,540
I understand you're keeping your distance because you've hurt him,

67
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:42,060
but what about your feelings for him? Did they disappear?

68
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:48,850
Kotaro-san was only a florist I used to frequent. Everything is back to normal.

69
00:06:48,850 --> 00:06:54,070
I'm back to my true self, where I'm meant to be.

70
00:06:56,770 --> 00:07:02,250
Makoto-chan, remember when we first met? It was cherry blossom season.

71
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:05,550
I do! You came at me with an umbrella.

72
00:07:06,290 --> 00:07:09,620
Now it's cherry fruit season.

73
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,930
Tasty.

74
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:24,460
You know, cherries can never return to their blossoms, but they are delicious.

75
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:49,200
Tasty.

76
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:58,550
This is delicious.

77
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,030
<i>[Ubars Inc.]</i>

78
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:15,420
Excuse me.

79
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:21,650
- Welcome.
- Over here.

80
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:24,380
- Right.
- Ready and...

81
00:08:26,790 --> 00:08:28,430
Thanks, it's so heavy.

82
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:31,150
This is nothing compared to hauling our CEO around.

83
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:32,930
It happens when he's drunk,

84
00:08:32,930 --> 00:08:36,180
especially during our flower viewing party this year.

85
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:38,730
- Oh, with the bunny costume.
- Yes.

86
00:08:38,730 --> 00:08:42,720
Apparently, his girlfriend had just dumped him back then.

87
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:46,170
- "Dumped him"?
- He had never experienced heartbreak before,

88
00:08:46,170 --> 00:08:50,630
and he kept whining about getting back together with her.

89
00:08:54,580 --> 00:08:58,710
Excuse me, but is the CEO in today?

90
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:03,000
<i>[Hey, there's something I want to talk about.]</i>

91
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:07,200
If only I had a bit more time.

92
00:09:11,850 --> 00:09:14,460
Hello. Are you here for the delivery?

93
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:17,870
Do you need anything?

94
00:09:19,310 --> 00:09:22,190
You were the ex-boyfriend.

95
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:28,270
Were you following her after you two broke up?

96
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:31,740
What? You think I'm the stalker?

97
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:35,550
You approached her, claiming love at first sight, hoping to reunite.

98
00:09:38,260 --> 00:09:41,930
Exactly. And what's so wrong with that?

99
00:09:41,930 --> 00:09:44,620
I've done nothing to harm her.

100
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:46,760
I'm just telling her I love her.

101
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:50,420
Why were you there the day she fell?

102
00:09:50,420 --> 00:09:53,760
You even bothered to hide your face.

103
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,730
Do I need to tell you?

104
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:02,880
- <i>Cheers!
- Cheers.</i>

105
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:06,120
- <i>We heard you the first time.
- Who cares?</i>

106
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:10,430
- <i>That siren is close.
- Sounds like it's by the shrine.</i>

107
00:10:10,430 --> 00:10:12,810
<i>You've finally shown yourself, Ritsu-san.</i>

108
00:10:12,810 --> 00:10:15,790
<i>Why are you even wearing this?</i>

109
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:19,350
<i>Because I get teary when I drink.</i>

110
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:23,030
<i>- He's really feeling the heartbreak.
- Come on, cheer up!</i>

111
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:28,000
I don't like people seeing me cry.

112
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:33,560
You are annoying.

113
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:39,210
Anyway, don't worry about Makoto-san. She has me.

114
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:49,270
Well, I'm sure it's rough to hear she's dating Ritsu-kun now.

115
00:10:49,270 --> 00:10:51,350
That's not why I'm wallowing.

116
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:56,140
Ritsu-kun also had it rough, having been forgotten this whole time.

117
00:10:57,360 --> 00:11:00,150
So I guess she remembers him.

118
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:04,520
What do you mean? She remembers you too, right?

119
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:10,680
There‚Äôs something more painful than being forgotten.

120
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:12,380
What do you mean?

121
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:21,440
Even if we experience the same thing, it doesn‚Äôt mean we see eye to eye on it.

122
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,110
Are you hallucinating?

123
00:11:23,110 --> 00:11:24,810
All right, no more alcohol.

124
00:11:24,810 --> 00:11:28,220
- What? Why? Just one more glass.
- No.

125
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:41,060
Sorry I had you come to the office.

126
00:11:41,060 --> 00:11:44,420
It's fine. I'm the one who called you.

127
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:55,450
When we went to the aquarium, I wore an outfit I'd apparently bought for you.

128
00:11:55,450 --> 00:11:58,550
Sure. It made me happy.

129
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:00,500
I know.

130
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:06,620
I wanted to remain beautiful and mature, just as you'd liked.

131
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:09,940
That's why I wore it again.

132
00:12:09,940 --> 00:12:15,570
I thought I'd return to the way I was, now that my memories were back.

133
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:19,090
Except...

134
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:22,860
I was wrong.

135
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:29,110
After I first lost my memories, I frantically searched for myself.

136
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:32,390
But there never was a "real me" to find.

137
00:12:33,580 --> 00:12:37,660
I think I had always been my real self.

138
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:42,650
I acted like I had a personality, no matter whom I was with.

139
00:12:42,650 --> 00:12:47,220
There was never a version of me that was definitively myself.

140
00:12:54,110 --> 00:13:00,120
Still, if there's one thing I'm certain about,

141
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:05,780
it's that forcing you to smile with that outfit is not "me."

142
00:13:09,530 --> 00:13:11,160
Ritsu.

143
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:16,130
I can't stay with you anymore.

144
00:13:18,910 --> 00:13:20,790
I'm sorry.

145
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:37,650
At first, I was desperate to bring back the Makoto-san I used to know.

146
00:13:40,770 --> 00:13:42,740
But now...

147
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:52,510
I love the person you've become: the person who is critical of her definitive self.

148
00:13:55,210 --> 00:14:01,800
Would you... please give me another chance?

149
00:14:04,890 --> 00:14:06,500
I'm sorry.

150
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:12,760
I knew it.

151
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:38,330
Just one last time, okay?

152
00:14:55,310 --> 00:14:57,500
I'm all charged up.

153
00:15:01,930 --> 00:15:03,870
Don't look so upset.

154
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:06,990
This is my second rejection, after all.

155
00:15:10,030 --> 00:15:13,990
Come get angry at my lie when you remember, okay?

156
00:15:16,970 --> 00:15:20,180
Farewell, Makoto-san.

157
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,030
Farewell.

158
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:48,980
At least this time I was able to see her off with a smile.

159
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:33,390
<i>I recommend you light it in someone's company though.</i>

160
00:16:33,390 --> 00:16:36,400
<i>Because you might feel melancholic.</i>

161
00:16:38,420 --> 00:16:42,530
Even though I'm alone, I guess I can still light it.

162
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,890
What a pleasant scent.

163
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,150
<i>Again?</i>

164
00:17:04,150 --> 00:17:06,100
- <i>Again?
- Yes, again!</i>

165
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:08,050
<i>Really?</i>

166
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:13,040
<i>Take care, Makoto.</i>

167
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:22,000
<i>I know this scent from my childhood.</i>

168
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:26,090
And also...

169
00:17:39,010 --> 00:17:40,900
<i>What are you doing?</i>

170
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:45,640
<i>Great question.</i>

171
00:17:48,050 --> 00:17:55,000
<i>This floral scent always reminds me... spring is on its way.</i>

172
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:58,530
<i>Oh, the winter daphne.</i>

173
00:17:58,530 --> 00:18:02,900
<i>- "Winter daphne"?
- Yes. It's a shrub that blooms in early spring.</i>

174
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:05,240
<i>There's one by the park entrance there.</i>

175
00:18:07,490 --> 00:18:13,330
<i>Whenever I catch this scent,</i>

176
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:17,190
<i>I always get anxious and lonely.</i>

177
00:18:19,170 --> 00:18:22,790
<i>Sorry, that must be strange. I really don't know about flowers.</i>

178
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:24,730
<i>It's not strange at all.</i>

179
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:33,020
<i>You're free to think flowers are beautiful, delicious, or lonesome.</i>

180
00:18:37,810 --> 00:18:40,980
<i>I'd say they smell nice and lonely.</i>

181
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:45,860
<i>"Free"?</i>

182
00:18:47,610 --> 00:18:49,610
<i>I guess it‚Äôs my choice.</i>

183
00:18:51,390 --> 00:18:54,970
<i>They do smell nice and lonely.</i>

184
00:19:00,710 --> 00:19:04,390
<i>I'll walk you home since you seem lonely.</i>

185
00:19:04,390 --> 00:19:07,350
<i>- Thanks.
- See you.</i>

186
00:19:16,340 --> 00:19:20,150
A flower that blooms in early spring...

187
00:19:22,180 --> 00:19:28,190
I've been in love with Kotaro-san for a while now.

188
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:36,960
<i>You'd prefer gift certificates over flowers, right?</i>

189
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:38,690
<i>Yes.</i>

190
00:19:38,690 --> 00:19:43,540
<i>Maybe you don't appreciate flowers because you're lonely.</i>

191
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:47,860
<i>- What?
- Flowers serve no practical use.</i>

192
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:50,520
<i>You buy them only if there's a recipient,</i>

193
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:54,350
<i>like someone important or precious to you.</i>

194
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:56,970
<i>Don't people buy flowers for themselves?</i>

195
00:19:57,650 --> 00:20:00,570
<i>Exactly, someone important.</i>

196
00:20:02,090 --> 00:20:04,840
<i>Sorry, I'm acting like a know-it-all.</i>

197
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:07,540
<i>- Ignore me.
- It's fine.</i>

198
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:14,050
<i>You've inspired me to get a gift for my special someone, too.</i>

199
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:27,490
<i>I can have this design made in two weeks.</i>

200
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:29,480
<i>Thank you.</i>

201
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:32,510
<i>I hope your recipient will like it.</i>

202
00:20:32,510 --> 00:20:36,200
<i>Yes. It's a gift for someone I love.</i>

203
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,980
<i>How wonderful.</i>

204
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,720
<i>Kotaro-san.</i>

205
00:20:59,770 --> 00:21:02,220
<i>If you have time, would you like to...</i>

206
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:07,460
<i>I'm sorry. I've never seen you in that way before.</i>

207
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:15,250
<i>You're free to think of flowers however you want,</i>

208
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:20,080
But I'm a florist. Come back if you ever find flowers beautiful.

209
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:35,320
So you were never going to be worn after all.

210
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:49,810
Makoto hasn't come to visit recently, has she?

211
00:21:51,270 --> 00:21:54,010
- She won't be dropping by anymore.
- What?

212
00:21:54,630 --> 00:21:56,300
Why's that?

213
00:22:00,650 --> 00:22:03,070
Sorry, what?

214
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:07,020
I said I was dumped for a second time.

215
00:22:09,050 --> 00:22:14,230
I told you not to meddle with Makoto-san, so I figured I'd tell you myself.

216
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:17,350
She and I are no longer...

217
00:22:17,350 --> 00:22:23,840
Oh, great. So, that means Asahi is the closest to Makoto-san now.

218
00:22:24,830 --> 00:22:27,300
He also lied by telling her they were friends.

219
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:28,810
What?

220
00:22:29,630 --> 00:22:31,090
Asahi was lying?

221
00:22:31,090 --> 00:22:33,200
You didn't know?

222
00:22:34,190 --> 00:22:37,100
Asahi was only a coworker of hers.

223
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:39,370
They were all lies,

224
00:22:39,370 --> 00:22:44,300
including my "love at first sight" and you being her ex.

225
00:22:44,970 --> 00:22:50,060
I guess that shows just how much we all cared about her.

226
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:54,830
I really want her to be happy.

227
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:04,450
But I couldn't be the one to make her smile from the heart.

228
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:41,970
- Hey there.
- Hey.

229
00:23:42,740 --> 00:23:45,620
I see. You two broke up.

230
00:23:46,570 --> 00:23:48,620
Right.

231
00:23:48,620 --> 00:23:52,240
He'll be fine. He's a strong guy.

232
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:58,440
So how are your memories?

233
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:03,110
A lot has happened since I initially lost them,

234
00:24:03,110 --> 00:24:08,870
but I'm glad it let me find this job, and become friends with you.

235
00:24:10,790 --> 00:24:13,460
Sorry, I didn't mean...

236
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:16,700
Don't be. I'm happy you feel that way.

237
00:24:18,170 --> 00:24:20,570
I've decided to focus on work for now.

238
00:24:20,570 --> 00:24:25,830
Still, it'd be nice if I could recall what happened the day I fell.

239
00:24:54,640 --> 00:24:56,490
Asahi-kun.

240
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,010
What're you doing out here?

241
00:25:03,010 --> 00:25:05,010
I was heading home from the office.

242
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:11,450
I heard you weren't really friends with Makoto.

243
00:25:12,530 --> 00:25:14,660
No, I wasn't.

244
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:17,540
- I'm sorry.
- Don't apologize to me.

245
00:25:17,540 --> 00:25:20,220
You see, I...

246
00:25:29,380 --> 00:25:34,380
If you're in this area often, do you pass by my store as well?

